<h2><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Globalisation on Rural Economy&nbsp; = (agriculture + rural social order) :&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#666666">+ ves</span></span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Agricultural&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">shift to cash crops (BT cotton, tobacco) ;&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">new technologies: drip irrigation, farm machines</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Contract farming : PepsiCo (tomatoes, Karnataka) =&gt;better farmer income</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">&nbsp;better labour market</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">export market</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">e-commerce allowing recognition and sale of GI goods.e.g: Nolen Gud by Bengal</span></span></span></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#666666">- ves</span></span></span></h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Poverty alleviation efforts undermined as MSP and subsidies challenged in WTO by developed countries</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Agricultural&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">seed price increased ; Single crops =&gt; no diversification =&gt; more vulnerable to vagaries of monsoon&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">feminisation of agriculture</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Big farmers benefitted more =&gt; Wage labourers =&gt; rural-urban migration</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Contract farming =&gt; not sustainable, only elite products (not of daily use)</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Agri extension services suffered : MNC agents selling seeds, pesticides also providing information (vested interest)</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Macro level&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Regional inequalities up (dry regionsâ€™ agriculture is underdeveloped, e.g. Eastern UP, Bihar)&nbsp;</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Social&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Lost traditional knowledge of farming (cultural&nbsp; loss) : now advocating ZBNF</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">rural distress : marriages dowry etc customs changed =&gt; demand more money =&gt; marginal farmer feeling distress</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Environmental&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">pesticide more = land degradation + ecological crisis in rural area</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Cultural: loss of traditional languages. e.g: Aka-Bo of Andaman, Gondi in central India</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">MSME: local handicrafts and artisans suffer in face of MNCs and dumping of Chinese products.</span></span></span></li></ol>
